{"word":"παρισόομαι","slug":"παρισόομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>παρισόομαι</b></el> <el>(aor1 <el>-ισώθην</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἴσος'><el>ἴσος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to make oneself equal to, measure oneself with</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to be made equal</i> or <i>like to</i>, <el>τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}